<br>
Quick as a cat, Anari danced around Khasirath, cutting him here and there.  Viciously, Khasirath battled Anari looking for the one perfect opening to end this all.  Then, with a single look to Creapiing, they both plunged off the bridge in a tangled mass.<br>
<br>
Creapiing raced to the edge in time to see Khasirath hitting at Anari as they plunged into the ice covered river.  The cracking of the ice gave off a sound that was almost inaudible against the sound of every one of Anaris bones breaking as she hit the ice first.  Creapiing wasnt sure whether the screams she heard were only in her mind.  She raced across the ice and grabbed Khasiraths cloak.  <br>
<br>
Her feet scrabbled for traction.  Khasiraths dead weight was pulling her toward the opening.  Creapiing fell to the ice, hoping that the length of her body against the ice would give her enough footing to pull Khasirath out.  Visions of his smiling face in her office, of the way he blushed, of the strength of his presence passed through her mind.  Tensing every muscle, Creapiing pulled steadily and with all her strength to draw Khasirath out onto the ice.<br>
<br>
Odd splotches of green stood out on his normally Bluish skin.  Poison.  The freezing water had highlighted every bit of poison.  Creapiing dipped her hands into the frigid water and retrieved a handful of ice chips.  Quickly she placed the ice on each poisoned wound, and placed a large chunk in his mouth. <br>
<br>
Then, with a loud prayer to Innoruuk, Creapiing began the slow and painful process of transferring her health to the fading body of Khasirath.  Again and again the two of them were surrounded by a red glow as she prayed, chanted and cast her feeble magic to save Khasiraths life.  Finally exhausted, she slumped across his body on the frozen river. <p>Creapiing V'Etch<BR>
